#: src/metadata.md:1
msgid "Python Project Metadata"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:3
msgid ""
"maturin supports [PEP 621](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0621/), you "
"can specify python package metadata in `pyproject.toml`. maturin merges "
"metadata from `Cargo.toml` and `pyproject.toml`, `pyproject.toml` take "
"precedence over `Cargo.toml`."
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:7
msgid "Here is a `pyproject.toml` example from PEP 621 for reference purpose:"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:9
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[project]\n"
"name = \"spam\"\n"
"version = \"2020.0.0\"\n"
"description = \"Lovely Spam! Wonderful Spam!\"\n"
"readme = \"README.rst\"\n"
"requires-python = \">=3.8\"\n"
"license = {file = \"LICENSE.txt\"}\n"
"keywords = [\"egg\", \"bacon\", \"sausage\", \"tomatoes\", \"Lobster "
"Thermidor\"]\n"
"authors = [\n"
"  {email = \"hi@pradyunsg.me\"},\n"
"  {name = \"Tzu-Ping Chung\"}\n"
"]\n"
"maintainers = [\n"
"  {name = \"Brett Cannon\", email = \"brett@python.org\"}\n"
"]\n"
"classifiers = [\n"
"  \"Development Status :: 4 - Beta\",\n"
"  \"Programming Language :: Python\"\n"
"]\n"
"\n"
"dependencies = [\n"
"  \"httpx\",\n"
"  \"gidgethub[httpx]>4.0.0\",\n"
"  \"django>2.1; os_name != 'nt'\",\n"
"  \"django>2.0; os_name == 'nt'\"\n"
"]\n"
"\n"
"[project.optional-dependencies]\n"
"test = [\n"
"  \"pytest < 5.0.0\",\n"
"  \"pytest-cov[all]\"\n"
"]\n"
"\n"
"[project.urls]\n"
"homepage = \"example.com\"\n"
"documentation = \"readthedocs.org\"\n"
"repository = \"github.com\"\n"
"changelog = \"github.com/me/spam/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md\"\n"
"\n"
"[project.scripts]\n"
"spam-cli = \"spam:main_cli\"\n"
"\n"
"[project.gui-scripts]\n"
"spam-gui = \"spam:main_gui\"\n"
"\n"
"[project.entry-points.\"spam.magical\"]\n"
"tomatoes = \"spam:main_tomatoes\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:59
msgid "Add Python dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:61
msgid ""
"To specify python dependencies, add a list `dependencies` in a `[project]` "
"section in the `pyproject.toml`. This list is equivalent to "
"`install_requires` in setuptools:"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:63
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[project]\n"
"name = \"my-project\"\n"
"dependencies = [\"flask~=1.1.0\", \"toml==0.10.0\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:69
msgid "Add console scripts"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:71
msgid ""
"Pip allows adding so called console scripts, which are shell commands that "
"execute some function in you program. You can add console scripts in a "
"section `[project.scripts]`. The keys are the script names while the values "
"are the path to the function in the format `some.module.path:class."
"function`, where the `class` part is optional. The function is called with "
"no arguments. Example:"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:74
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[project.scripts]\n"
"get_42 = \"my_project:DummyClass.get_42\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:79
msgid "Add trove classifiers"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:81
msgid ""
"You can also specify [trove classifiers](https://pypi.org/classifiers/) "
"under `project.classifiers`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:83
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[project]\n"
"name = \"my-project\"\n"
"classifiers = [\"Programming Language :: Python\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:89
msgid "Add SPDX license expressions"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:91
msgid ""
"A practical string value for the license key has been purposefully left out "
"by PEP 621 to allow for a future PEP to specify support for [SPDX](https://"
"spdx.org/licenses/) expressions."
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:95
msgid ""
"To use SPDX license expressions, you can specify it in `Cargo.toml` instead:"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:97
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[package]\n"
"name = \"my-project\"\n"
"license = \"MIT OR Apache-2.0\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
